    "Lloyd R. Bailey": ") are \u201cunclean\u201d because of \u201can\nindeterminate form of movement,\u201d29 is that any less the case than\nindividuals in a herd of \u201cclean\u201d quadrupeds that mill around at\nrandom? Or herds that, when frightened, rush blindly in all direc-\ntions? Or schools of \u201cclean\u201d fish? Why are all land \u201cswarmers\u201d\nforbidden for food ("
